Check if the number is even or odd using modulus and conditional operators
package Program;
import java.util.*;
public class Sample1 {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		int a=sc.nextInt();
		System.out.println((a%2==0)?"even":"odd");
    sc.close();
	}
}

Write a program to calculate area of circle and print the result.
package Program;
import java.util.*;
public class Sample2 {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		int a=sc.nextInt();
		float pi=3.14f;
		float c=a*a*pi;
		System.out.print(c);
		sc.close();
	}
}

Write a program which uses the arithmetic operators
package Program;
import java.util.*;
public class Sample3 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		int a=sc.nextInt();
		int b=sc.nextInt();
		System.out.println("Addition of two numbers : "+(a+b));
		System.out.println("Subtraction of two numbers : "+(a-b));
		System.out.println("Multiplication of two numbers : "+(a*b));
		System.out.println("Division of two numbers : "+(a/b));
		System.out.println("Remainder o two numbers : "+(a%b));
        sc.close();
	}
}

Write a program to get the input about employee details and print
package Program;
import java.util.*;
public class Sample4 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
		String EmpName=sc.nextLine();
		int EmpId= sc.nextInt();
		sc.nextLine();
		String EmpRoll=sc.nextLine();
		String EmpFrom=sc.nextLine();
		System.out.println(EmpName+" "+EmpId+" "+EmpRoll+" "+EmpFrom);
        sc.close();
	}

}

Explain the different types of variables using example program
Types o variable:
  * Local Variable
  * Instance Variable
  * Static variable
  * Parameter variable
Local Variable:
  it can declared inside the method body and it is used only inside the method body.
Example:
  import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public void add(){
        int a=10; // local variable
        int b=20; // local variable
        System.out.print(a+b);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Main obj = new Main();  // object creation
        obj.add(); // calling the method
    }
}
Instance Variable:
  it can be declared out side the method and inside the class.
  it is a non static variable
  it can be accessed only by object creation
Example:
 import java.util.*;
class Main{
    int a=10; // instance variable
    int b=20; // instance variable
    int c=30; // instance variable
    public void add(){
        System.out.print(a+b+c);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Main obj = new Main();  // object creation
        obj.add(); // calling the method    
    }
}
Static Variable:
  it can be declared out side the method and inside the class.
  Static keyword is used.
  object creation is not necessary.
Example:
import java.util.*;
class Main{
    static int c=30;  // static variable
    public static void add(){ // static method
        int a=10;
        int b=20;
        System.out.print(a+b);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        // object creation is not neccessary
        System.out.print(Main.c); // calling static variable.
        Main.add(); // calling static method.
    }
}
Parameter Variable:
  passing values to the methods.
 import java.util.*;
class Main{
    public void add(int a,int b){
        System.out.print(a+b);
    }
    public static void main(String[] args){
        Main obj =new Main(); // object creation
        obj.add(10,20); // passing parameter 
       
    }
}
